    "notes": "Latvian has initial stress in the vast majority of native words. Enclitics and some loanwords may shift stress, but for G2P purposes initial-stress is the reliable default. Long vowels (ā ē ī ū) and circumflex/falling tones (ar̃) mark quantity/tone, not stress position. Source: Nau (1998), Latvian; Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latvian_phonology"
